Regarding triple extraction, the existing challenges arise from computational linguistics. A common problem refers to non-trivial sentence fragments such as compound nouns and phrasal verbs. For example, a phrasal verb such as ‘to search for’ it not easy to map to a triple; take the sentence ‘I was searching my cupboard for my pills’ could result either in a triple \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
